27\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37412,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/22\/muhammad-forgiving-generous\/","url_meta":{"origin":32657,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Mercy: I will find Muhammad forgiving and generous","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 22, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019d ibn Abi Waqqas reported: On the day Mecca was liberated, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, granted general amnesty to all of the people except for four men and two women. They were \u2018Ikramah ibn Abi Jahl, Abdullah ibn Khatal, Maqis ibn Subabah, and Abdullah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13714,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/04\/24\/sea-water-pure-halal\/","url_meta":{"origin":32657,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Water: Sea water is pure, animals halal to eat","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 24, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was asked about sea water and he said, \u201cIts water is purifying for ablution,\u00a0and its dead animals are lawful to eat.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \"It is the opinion of most of the jurists among the companions of the Prophet, peace\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"}